



To Captain Joshua Lewisat Fredericksburgh.Sir,
[Winchester, 26 June 1756]



It is Colonel Washingtons Orders that you send off all the Officers at Fredericksburgh to this placeexcept one Subaltern, whom you are to keep there in case more draughts should arrive. What Draughts are now with you, must be marched up by the Officers coming to this place.1
Lieutenant Lowry is the Subaltern who is to remain with you. I am &c.

G:M. aid de camp.
Winchester, June 26th 1756.

